  "instructions": [
    "In a saucepan, combine miso paste, rice vinegar, fish sauce, sugar, and sesame oil. Heat over medium heat, whisking until the mixture is smooth and slightly thickened.",
    "Add the mussels to the saucepan and cook, stirring occasionally, until they're heated through and starting to open, about 5 minutes.",
    "Meanwhile, toast the baguette slices until crispy.",
    "To assemble the bao, place a few mussels on each toasted baguette slice, followed by a spoonful of the miso sauce, some cilantro, and pickled carrots.",
    "Sprinkle with smoked chili flakes and serve immediately."
